did.unittitle: Roger Mennevée collection of research material relating to French political, social, economic, and artistic life
did.abstract: Roger Mennevée was a researcher, journalist, editor and publisher of a private newsletter: Les Documents Politiques, Diplomatiques et Financiers. The archive was assembled by Mr. Mennevée from the more than 50 years of extensive research in the preparation of his newsletter. The majority of the collection was obtained in 1965, while the rest was donated in 1969, on the occasion of Mennevée's retirement. As a collection of research items, the Mennevée archive is an exhaustive mine of information which documents social, political, economic and artistic life in France between 1910 and 1969.

bioghist.head: Administrative/Biographical History
bioghist.p: Roger Mennevée was a researcher, journalist, editor and publisher of a private newsletter: Les Documents Politiques, Diplomatiques et Financiers. Les Documents was widely considered, in academic circles, to be one of the best informed newsletters of its kind. The archive was assembled by Mr. Mennevée from the more than 50 years of extensive research in the preparation of his newsletter. The majority of the collection was obtained in 1965, while the rest was donated in 1969, on the occasion of Mennevée's retirement.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Collection contains material related to Menevée's career as editor and publisher of Les informations politiques et financières and Les documents politiques, diplomatiques, et financiers. Includes clippings, correspondence, periodicals, pamphlets, broadsheets, government publications, and bulletins. Mennevée developed an extensive collection of biographical and subject files which provided the resources for his research and publications. The bulk of the files concern political, economic, and diplomatic life between 1914 and 1940 collected from French and foreign presses, the Stock Exchange, financial companies, and official announcements.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The Roger Mennevee's original organization of the collection has been maintained. Mennevee collected and maintained files on a huge array of topics, which were categorized into the following 9 series:

1) Archive of Contemporary Biography 2) Press Archive 3) Espionage and Secret Service Archive 4) Secret Societies and Occultism 5) Political Archive 6) Economic and Financial Archive 7) Loose Folders and Additions 8) Catalogs, Listings and Indices 9) Documentation Générale
